body.name: ASUS ROG Strix Z790-A Gaming WiFi D4 LGA1700(Intel 14th& 13th & 12th Gen) ATX gaming motherboard(16+1 power stages,DDR4,4xM.2 slots, PCIe 5.0,WiFi 6E,USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 Type-C with PD 3.0 up to 30W)
body.merchantInfo: Sold by Amazon Warehouse and Fulfilled by Amazon.
features: Intel LGA 1700 socket: Ready for 13th Gen Intel Core processors and 12th Gen Intel Core, Pentium Gold and Celeron Processors
Robust Power Solution: 16 plus 1 power solution rated for 70A per stage with dual ProCool II power connectors, high-quality alloy chokes, and durable capacitors to support multi-core processors
Optimized VRM Thermals: Massive heatsinks with integrated I/O cover and high-conductivity thermal pads.
Ample M.2 Support: One PCIe 4.0 M.2 slot with a heatsink and backplate, and three PCIe 4.0 M.2 slots with heatsinks

Abundant Connectivity: USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 Type-C rear I/O port and additional front-panel connector with PD 3.0 up to 30W, USB 3.2 Gen 2 and Gen 1 ports, PCIe 5.0 x16 SafeSlot, HDMI 2.1, and DisplayPort 1.4
High-Performance Networking: On-board WiFi 6E (802.11ax) and Intel 2.5 Gb Ethernet with ASUS LANGuard
Intelligent Control: ASUS-exclusive AI Overclocking, AI Cooling II, AI Networking, and Two-Way AI Noise Cancelation simplifies setup and improves performance
DIY-friendly Design: PCIe Slot Q-Release, M.2 Q-Latch, pre-mounted I/O shield, Q-LED, BIOS FlashBack button, BIOS FlashBack LED, and Clear CMOS button
Renowned Software: Bundled 60-day AIDA64 Extreme trial subscription and intuitive UEFI BIOS dashboard with integrated MemTest86
body.description: The ASUS ROG Strix Z790-A Gaming WiFi D4 white and silver scheme motherboard is designed with boosted power delivery and optimized cooling to cope with the demands of powerful 13th Generation Intel® Core™ processors. Along with Wi-Fi 6 and PCI Express® 5.0 for superfast transfer speeds and storage, ROG Strix Z790-A Gaming WiFi D4 is ready to take the helm of your clean and neat white gaming gear.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Republic of Gamers (ROG), part of the ASUS family, is dedicated to creating innovative hardcore gaming hardware for gamers. ROG is committed to providing the absolute best performance and quality from its complete line of products. ROG is for those keen on the finest gaming hardware and software as it enables the ultimate computing experience for gamers and enthusiasts worldwide. It incorporates a stylish gamer-focused design, merging the excitement of gaming with a unique premium style. ROG STRIX Z790-A GAMING WIFI D4 ASUS ROG Strix Z790-A Gaming WiFi D4, Intel Z790 LGA 1700 ATX motherboard, 16 + 1 power stages, DDR4, four M.2 slots, PCIe 5.0, WiFi 6E, USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 Type-C with PD 3.0 up to 30W, Aura Sync RGB Intel LGA 1700 socket: Ready for 13th Gen Intel Core processors & 12th Gen Intel Core, Pentium Gold and Celeron Processors Robust Power Solution: 16 + 1 power solution rated for 70A per stage with dual ProCool II power connectors, high-quality alloy chokes, and durable capacitors to support multi-core processors Optimized VRM Thermals: Massive heatsinks with integrated I/O cover and high-conductivity thermal pads. Ample M.2 Support: One PCIe 4.0 M.2 slot with a heatsink and backplate, and three PCIe 4.0 M.2 slots with heatsinks Abundant Connectivity: USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 Type-C rear I/O port & additional front-panel connector w/PD 3.0 up to 30W, USB 3.2 Gen 2 & Gen 1 ports, PCIe 5.0 x16 SafeSlot, HDMI 2.1, & DisplayPort 1.4 High-Performance Networking: On-board WiFi 6E (802.11ax) and Intel 2.5 Gb Ethernet with ASUS LANGuard Intelligent Control: ASUS-exclusive AI Overclocking, AI Cooling II, AI Networking, and Two-Way AI Noise Cancelation simplifies setup and improves performance Immersive Gaming Audio: ALC4080 with Savitech SV3H712 amplifier, along with DTS Sound Unbound and Sonic Studio III

AI OVERCLOCKING Tuning is now faster and smarter than ever before. ASUS AI Overclocking profiles the CPU and cooling to predict the optimal configuration and push the system to its limits. Predicted values can be engaged automatically or used as a launching ground for further experimentation. PCIE 5.0 The top PCIe 5.0 x16 SafeSlot is well-equipped for the increased size and bandwidth of next-gen graphics cards. Zippy storage options abound with four PCIe 4.0 M.2 slots, all featuring robust heatsinks to maximize performance. POWER DESIGN POWER ARCHITECTURE 16 + 1 power stages rated to 70A each deliver ample current in order to drive 13th and 12th Gen Intel Core Processors through any workload with ease. ALLOY CHOKES AND DURABLE CAPACITORS Hi-end chokes and durable capacitors are engineered to resist extreme temperatures, enabling performance that exceeds industry standards. DUAL PROCOOL II POWER CONNECTORS​ ProCool II connectors are precision-built to ensure flush contact with PSU power lines. A metal sheath improves heat dissipation and lowers electrical impedance. SIX-LAYER PCB A multi-layered printed circuit board design quickly dissipates heat around the voltage regulators to improve overall system stability and provide the CPU with more overclocking headroom.

MEMORY OPTIMEM III With proprietary memory trace layout tweaks that improve signal integrity and mitigate noise, OptiMem III allows memory kits to run at lower latencies, reduced voltages, and operate at higher frequencies. COOLING VRM HEATSINKS Covering the power solution are two thick heatsinks with strategic airflow channels for increased heat dissipation while powering high-performance Intel 13th Gen processors. NETWORKING WIFI 6E Onboard WiFi 6E technology takes advantage of newly available spectrum in the 6 GHz band to provide up to seven 160 MHz channels for ultrafast throughput and better performance in dense wireless environments. 2.5G Ethernet Low-latency gaming, speedy file transfers, and high-resolution video streaming are among the many perks of onboard Intel 2.5 Gbps Ethernet.

USB USB 3.2 GEN 2X2 The Strix Z790-A comes loaded with two USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 Type-C connectors for speedy data transfers up to 20 Gbps. One is a port on the rear I/O; the other can be attached to the chassis front panel and it also features Power Delivery (PD) 3.0 technology to quickly charge devices up to 30W. SUPREMEFX ROG SupremeFX is a unique blend of hardware and software technologies that provide superior audio. The Strix Z790-A implementation features the ALC4080 codec for high-resolution playback up to 32-bit/384 kHz across all channels. Front-panel output is streamed through the integrated Savitech amplifier that can drive high-fidelity acoustics to a wide variety of speakers and headsets. ID DESIGN UNDENIABLY ROG STRIX​ The ROG Strix Z790-A boldly embraces the light, for an alternate take on build themes to its dark and brooding brother, the Strix Z790-F. Silver metallic heatsinks pop against a dark PCB backdrop and call attention to the board's high capacity for thermal management. A transparent layer on the I/O shield adds a unique touch and emphasizes the customizable RGB logo below. The whole design is tied together with ROG-centric detailing on the board, heatsinks, and I/O shield for a vibrant and futuristic outlook. Pair the Strix Z790-A with other products from the diverse ROG ecosystem to create a fully-customized gaming setup that reflects your personal style.​

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great board for gamers and experts
reviews.reviewText: Having had other boards from MSI and Gigabyte in the same z90 series, I was flooded by the options in both the bios and the the software. The board works hassle free, and works well with rgb devices. There are a couple things that really sticks out as positives. The first is the button release for graphics card. It worked wonderfully when I had to replace my GPU. The second is the vast array of NVMe slots. It was amazing to have of the options. If you know your storage runs a bit hot, you can locate them in a cooler place.I would recommend this board to any seasoned computer person, who loves having the freedom to try a little tweaking of the configuration.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: great product easy to install but a key piece of information not included was that not all the software is installed and needs you to have a hard line internet connection to install all software (preferably through the armoury crate App, which is a nice feature) before you can use certain features like the wireless or Bluetooth. other than that i give it a 5 star

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars What happened to ASUS quality control? Why the crapware?
reviews.reviewText: Let me start by saying I will probably never buy another ASUS mobo ever again. The pain, frustration and countless hours wasted trying installing and uninstalling these detective mobos has left a surely bad impression.2 out of 3 of the mobos I ordered were defective. 1st I ordered the ASUS ROG Strix Z760-A D4. Upon installation and boot up I got CPU Fan header error (common for ASUS now, google it) even though my AOI was correctly hooked up and CPU header. Had to go into BIOS and ignore the error. Trying to use it for a short period of time it kept crashing windows 10. Completely unstable. So, had to tear down pc again and remove. In the meantime I ordered another onr but decided to upgrade to the same board but the DDR5 version. That board was fine and worked properly, however I then realized I could not overclock it, but it did not have that feature. Misleading marketing made me think I could.So, I decided to return this one and upgrade to the ROG Strix Z790-A DDR5. Again had to remove all components and start over. 2 days later I get the new Z790 installed and boot up. Guess what? The same issues as the 1st faulty one.CPY fan header errors. Wouldn’t post, had to flash BIOS multiple times because it would freeze a ROG logo screen. Complete frustration at this point. I’ve removed the board again and have return in process. But that’s not the end of the story. So I went ahead and purchased the MSI Z790 Edge from my local Best Buy and have that installed now and running like a dream. So now I’m unable to uninstall all of the ASUS bundleware crap (AI suite, Amory Crate, Sonic Suite companion, etc.) All this crapware is extremely hard to remove from windows. Many others are facing theses same issues. If you google “remove AI suite” or “remove Sonic Suite Companion” you’ll see what I mean. Total bundle crapware. I will never buy another ASUS mobo again! Total QC failure and the crapware is almost as bad as malware! Shame on ASUS!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Absolutely love this motherboard
reviews.reviewText: Motherboard looks and works amazing. Running it with an I7-12700 and 8 TB's of m.2. I have had no issues whatsoever. Would definitely purchase this again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Elegant looking and functional
reviews.reviewText: I upgraded from an Asus Prime Z390-A with i7 9700k. Now using this board with an i7 13700K. Install was fairly painless outside of invasive nature of motherboard removal/replacement. Most of the connectors on the new board were in the same place as the old one, making things easier. Only the USB 3.1 connection had moved significantly (from bottom to right side), necessitating cable movement in case. The black/white theme looks great, and the push-button GPU card removal function is very welcome! I also like the fact that the board has built-in WiFi and Bluetooth.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The board looks amazing and is easy to setup in BIOS. My only compliant is the labels for the sockets are difficult to read.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 8, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Really excited when I bought this. Came in on time. Everything is easy to install. One thing I did forget coming from Ryzen is that with Intel your supposed to install your drivers manually. With Ryzen all drivers should already be already installed. Plenty of USB slots for multiple devices. Hopefully my last build for a while.

La placa llegó en perfectas condiciones y antes de lo indicado, tiene buen diseño, ranuras m.2 más que suficiente y puertos sata, la bios tiene un dinero muy agradable y fácil de manejar, la opción para el manejo de los ventilador y ajustar la curva a tu manera es muy útil.El único problema que tuve fue que no me conectaba a Internet ni con cable ethernet, se soluciono fácil compartiéndolo con el celular mediante usb.Sin nada más que decir, es una mobo muy bonita, completa en todos los aspectos, muy recomendable

reviews.reviewTitle: HABER 5 ESTRELLAS EN TODO Y CALIFICACION EN GENERAL EN 3.. EXPLICO EN EL COMENTARIO
reviews.reviewText: Todo con el producto es una pasada, realmente al momento de abrirla ves el monstruo de MOTHERBOARD que es.. puedo decir sin haberla usado que es una pasada de componente. Le doy 5 estrellas en las caracteristicas, pero el pequeño y gran detalle por el que le doy 3 estrellas en general, es por que en la descripción en el apartado de "TIPO DE MEMORIA RAM" dice que es DDR5... y realmente es DDR4. Más abajo dice que es ddr4 pero no había llegado hasta ese punto, realmente nunca llegamos hasta el final de las descripciónes ya que lo importante esta arriba en ciertas partes. Por eso en el momento en que veo que dice DDR5 , me basto para comprarla. Solamente como comentario positivo, el vendedor de de poner bien en la descripción lo que es realmente, no se si fue error de el vendedor o realmente así lo puso pero bueno. Ya envié de regreso el paquete y espero no tener problemas con el reembolso.De ahí en más si piensas renovar motherboard y tus componentes son todavía DDR4, sin duda este sería una buena opción de compra ;)Saludos desde Aguascalientes :D
